title: Demand Deposits, Individual, Corporations, and Others, Weekly Reporting Member Banks for New York, NY
notes:
Series Is Presented Here As Four Variables--(1)--Orignal Data, 1919-1934 (2)--Original Data, 1934-1939 (3)--Original Data, 1939-1947 (4)--Original Data, 1946-1949. The Banking Act Of 1935 Substantially Changed The Method Used To Compute Net Demand Deposits, But Coverage Remained Substantially The Same. Source: Federal Reserve Board, Banking And Monetary Statistics, 1943.

This NBER data series m14132b appears on the NBER website in Chapter 14 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter14.html.
